content:
Job Responsibilities:

 * ESD / latch-up / EOS and IO library design;
 * Protection methodology for chip / system level design;
 * Device / system test methods and failure analysis.

 

Job Requirements:

 * Higher Diploma or Bachelor in Electronic Engineering or equivalent;
 * 3 years of relevant working experience;
 * Knowledge about semiconductor and device physics
 * Candidate with less experience will be considered as IC Design Engineer -
   Electrostatic Discharge and fresh graduate will also be considered;
 * Proficient in physical design tools (Cadence, Synopsys or Aether);
 * Be proactive, willing to learn and passionate in physical design;
 * Fluent English and Chinese (Mandarin) with good communication skill.

 

All applications will be treated in strict confidence and for recruitment
purpose only.

Job Responsibilities:

 * Provide multichannel customer service to local and overseas customers
   including the handling of calls, emails, online chats and enquires from
   various online channels;

 * Handle customer requests and resolve customer complaints to ensure customer
   satisfaction;

 * Solicit business opportunities through cross-selling and outbound calls to
   meet the sales and other business objectives;

 * Perform general support in centre to smoothen the daily operation;

 * Provide high quality service and handle daily operations according to the
   regulatory and compliance requirements to meet all the quality and service
   targets;

 * Perform duties on shift basis 7x24 to ensure the smooth and continuous
   operations.




Job Requirements:

 * Bachelor's degree or above in any discipline;

 * At least 2 years of call centre experience preferably in financial industry;

 * Excellent communication skill with strong customer-oriented mind set;

 * Pro-active, self-motivated, mature and pleasant personality;

 * Passed in HKSI 1, 7, 8 or equivalent & IIQE Paper 1, 2, 3 & 5 and MPF
   Intermediaries Examination is a must / is preferred;

 * Proficiency in both written and spoken English, Chinese and Putonghua.




Interested parties please send your full resume with present and expected
salary, and quoting reference number to Talent Acquisition Division by
clicking “Apply Now”. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and
refer to the page “Join Us”.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for
recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may
consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within
12 months of receipt.

